     Suppose you want to say, "A layer of snow."
     <br/>
     What you would do is first show (one of the many versions of snow) 
			and then show the thickness of the snow layer.
     <br/>
     Below I'm showing snow coming down by fluttering my fingers as I 
			moved my hands downward. Then I slide a "C" hand along the top of my 
			non-dominant forearm to show a layer of snow about 4 inches (8 
			centimeters) thick.
